anl48_bdvd_curr_dvd_health.description: The Dividend Health Score is calculated based on a company's fundamentals and ratings by rating agencies ranging from -100 to 100. The three significant ranges are: -100 to -50 where fundamentals suggest the company cannot sustain the current trend of dividend payments; -50 to 50 where the company can likely maintain the current trend of dividend payments; and 50 to 100 where the company has the ability to increase the amount of their dividend beyond their previous trend.

anl48_bp12m_dip.description: Total dividend projection in index points for 1 year in the future. It is the sum of the following calculation for each stock in the index.

anl48_bp12m_yld.description: Projected 12-month dividend yield. This is formulated by summing the next 12 months' dividends divided by the current stock price.

anl48_bp3y_dg.description: Projected dividend per share (DPS) growth rate over the next 3 years, based on the trailing 12-month dividend starting 3 years from today's date. This dividend amount is then divided by the current trailing 12-month dividend amount, annualized.

anl48_bpda.description: Next forecasted dividend per share (DPS) amount; it reveals per unit forecasts when looking at Master Limited Partnerships (MLPs). The forecasts are calculated by analysts based on 7 factors: Company Guidance, Health Score, Industry Analysis, Put-Call Parity, Trend Tool, Regression Analysis, and Analysts.

This topic addresses a company's ability to maintain a safe and healthy workplace environment. This includes creating a workplace free of injuries, fatalities, and illness (both chronic and acute, and physical and mental health) through technology, training, corporate culture, regulatory compliance, monitoring and testing, and personal protective equipment.

fnd21_volume_ttmdaily_energymanagement_c.description: Trailing 12 Months Volume of news articles relevant to Energy Management category of any company. This topic addresses indirect (Scope 2) greenhouse gas emissions through management of the use of energy in manufacturing and/or for the provision of products and services. It includes energy efficiency and intensity, energy mix, grid reliance, and other factors.

fnd21_volume_ttmdaily_fairlaborpractices.description: Trailing Twelve Months Volume of news articles relevant to Fair Labor Practices category of any company. This topic addresses management's ability to uphold commonly accepted labor standards in the workplace, including compliance with labor laws, internationally accepted norms and standards. At a minimum this includes ensuring basic human rights such as those outlined in ILO Standards related to child labor, forced or bonded labor, exploitative labor, fair wages and overtime pay, and other basic workers' rights. It also includes competitive and fair salaries, minimum wage policies, provision of benefits, all of which may relate to how a workforce is attracted, retained, and incentivized to act in the interests of the company. This topic addresses management's relationship with organized labor and freedom of association.

fnd21_volume_ttmdaily_ghgemissions_categ.description: Trailing Twelve Months Volume of news articles relevant to the GHG Emissions category of any company. This topic describes the management of direct (Scope 1) greenhouse gas emissions, including that from fuel consumption at stationary and non-stationary sources, exposure to regulation associated with carbon emissions, and relates to measures to mitigate emissions.

fnd21_volume_ttmdaily_lifecycleimpactsof.description: Trailing Twelve Months Volume of news articles relevant to Life Cycle Impact of Products and Services category of any company.

fnd21_volume_ttmdaily_productpackaging_c.description: Trailing 12 Months Volume of news articles relevant to Product Packaging category of any company. The topic addresses integrations of environmental, social, and governance (ESG) factors in characteristics of primary products and services provided or sold by a company. It addresses reduction of environmental externalities created during product life cycle, including impact of packaging, distribution, resource intensity of products in their use-phase, and end-of-life impacts of products. For service providers, it captures services which help customers reduce environmental and social impacts of their operations and/or their exposure to ESG risks. The topic covers company's ability to address customer and societal demand for more sustainable products and services as well as ability to meet evolving environmental and social regulatory rules.

fnd21_volume_ttmdaily_productqualityands.description: Trailing 12 Months Volume of news articles relevant to Product Quality and Safety category of any company. This topic addresses a company's ability to offer manufactured products and services that are safe, reliable, and of a high quality.

fnd21_volume_ttmdaily_supplychainmanagem.description: Trailing 12 Months Volume of news articles relevant to Supply Chain Management category of any company. This topic addresses the management of environmental, social, and governance risks within a company's supply chain. The supply chain is defined broadly and includes multiple tiers of suppliers from raw material suppliers to manufacturers of end products. It includes how companies screen, select, monitor, and engage with suppliers on environmental and social topics including environmental responsibility, human rights and labor practices, and ethics and corruption. The scope of the topic excludes issues related to impacts of climate change and other environmental and social factors on availability and pricing of key resources.

mws50_ess.description: EVENT SENTIMENT SCORE - A granular score between 0 and 100 that represents the news sentiment for a given entity by measuring various proxies sampled from the news. The score is determined by systematically matching stories typically categorized by financial experts as having short-term positive or negative financial or economic impact. Their ratings are encapsulated in an algorithm that generates a score range between 0-100 where higher values indicate more positive sentiment while values below 50 show negative sentiment.

mws50_vea.description: A value that represents the count of events for an entity (excluding neutral ones) measured over a rolling 91-day window in a particular package (Dow Jones, Web, or PR Editions). Only news items that match a RavenPack event category receiving an ESS score are included in the computation of AEV. Both events with an ESS score above and below 50 are counted by AEV, effectively signaling the volume of highly relevant news on the entity over the past 91 days. Events with ESS=50 are considered neutral and excluded from the computation
